description:
Black Knight discovers that Proctor is his parallel Earth counterpart. After realizing that her madness may be incurable, Sersi banishes herself to a pocket dimension. Plus, Ute the Watcher gets involved in the Avengers’ fray with the Gatherers!

Proctor appears in Manhattan, and the Avengers flies into their final confrontation with Proctor and his Gatherers. He has Sersi and Ute the Watcher as prisoners within a vortex of energy, allowing him to alter this Earth with artifacts from other parallel worlds. The Black Knight clashes with Proctor, who has just recently been discovered to be Black Knight's counterpart from another reality. But not only is he Dane Whitman and not only was he Sersi's Gann Josin, he also remains in possession of the Ebony Blade.

Crystal saves her two loves, Black Knight and Quicksilver, from Proctor. Sersi frees herself from Proctor's prison and uses the Ebony Blade to finish him off in cold blood. The damage done to her mind is not her fault, but it is irreversible. Ute the Watcher repairs the damage to Earth Proctor has done and in a final act, gives Sersi an alternate to death. For her own good and the good of Earth, she can leave this dimension. Unwillingly to let her go into exile alone, the Black Knight opts to go with her.

In a back-up short story, Hank Pym tests a psychoanalysis device on himself and must confront delusions in the form of talking ants making accusations of his character.

Also, the issue features pin-ups of Captain America by Tom Palmer and Deathcry by Steve Epting.

Some copies also included a pull-out poster.
name: The Last Gathering and A Bigger Man Than I...

description:
Overview

The Sentinel of Liberty—crushed by Americop!
name: Policing the Nation

description:
Cimmerian tribes and the forces of the Aquilonian fortress of Venarium go to war and conan is caught up in the middle.

*spoilers*

Conan and allies of cimmeria battle the enemies forces and despite loses on both sides turn the tide and wins the war. Afterward war breaks out between the various tribes.
name: Barbarians at the Gate!

description: Daredevil and Captain America join forces to face off with the tech-based terrors known as System Crash! But when the battle takes a vicious turn, a surprising but welcome ally enters the fray- Danny Rand, the Iron Fist!
name: Tree of Knowledge - Part 3: The Chernobyl Packet

description: Where in the (Beyonder´s) world have the Guardians Gone? More importantly, will Talon be able to get them out? Speaking of whom, Maphisto and Malevolence have suddenly taken a special interest in the feline Inhuman. Will the Amulet of the Ancient One fall into the hands of the demon and his daughter? Meanwhile, the Hawk God makes Aleta and Stakar pay a heavy price for their intrusion into the realm of the Cosmic Beings. And if you thought Scatan the Celestial was weird, wait until you see the Last Watcher! All this plus the Protege makes his big move in "Time is the rider that breaks us all"!
name: Time Is The Rider That Breaks Us All

description:
Featuring the marriage of Rick Jones and Marlo Chandler.

Note: Death Of The Endless, a DC/Vertigo character, makes a cameo at the wedding party, gifting Marlo a brush (making reference to Marlo's metaphorical "brush with death"). Neil Gaiman gave the cameo his blessing, and it was cleared by DC executive Paul Levitz, with the condition that Death's signature ankh had to be obscured.
name: We Are Gathered Here

description:
Spider-Man and Morbius fight but Morbius escapes in the vent shaft.In the building Vic Slaughter attacks Randolph who is dressed like an old lady and kills two CIA Agents. Vic tries to get him in his car but he is run over. Morbius then flies out on the car after Randolph with Spider-Man behind him. Spider-Man then webs himself on the car being dragged along and then grabs Morbius by the foot. The two both fall away from Randolph's get away car. Morbius then asks for Spider-Man's help and he helps he will let Spider-Man take him in to the cops. Spider-Man agrees.

As Martine lies trapped by the two CIA agents, Simon stroud prepairs to get revenge on Morbius and the two CIA Agents that got him locked up.

Meanwhile Morbius and Spider-Man get info from the cop Morbius knows that the victims of Randolph my be connected some how.

Back at the CIA Offices, they bring back Vic Slaughter and pay him a big amount of money to capture Randolph, Morbius, and Simon Stroud.

Menawhile Spider-Man and Morbius make it to the whereabouts of Randolph's net victim but they are to late. But Morbius sences that Randolph is not the killer of this man. As He investigates the area, Morbius is attacked by Simon Stroud who is the killer and then ends up holding a gun up to Morbius's face.
name: Dance of the Hunter II - Deceptions

description: Starfox asked Quasar to accompany him on 'family business'. They travelled to a remote moon for Starfox to meet with his brother: Thanos. A fight ensued when Quasar misunderstood Thanos' presence, not realizing that one day out of the year the brothers exchanged gifts peacefully. However, Thanos stole his gift meant for Starfox and the guards of the wronged party arrived to reclaim it. Starfox charmed the guards into believing they had reclaimed the item and Quasar managed to restain Thanos from killing them.
name: "Brothers In Arms"

description: Deadpool barely escapes with his life after duking it out against Malachi’s demons. Will the Secret Defenders be able to subdue Malachi before it’s too late? Shadowoman uses her newly bolstered powers, impressing Deadpool and teammate alike!
name: Resurrection Tango

description:
Issue #93 will change the way you think of THE SILVER SURFER forever! First, we have for you the start of the reign of exciting new penciler Bart Sears! He'll be joined in bringing to you the definitive new Surfer by Raymond Kryssing, inker supreme!
Together, they join the rest of the team to bring to you part one of the Surfer's return to Earth, featuring a flaming mad Human Torch!

Summary
The Silver Surfer has arrived on Earth and head to the Fantastic Four to tell them about Nova's death. He learns of Reed's death and tells Johnny and Ben the bad news. The Human Torch becomes angry and decides to take his anger out on the Surfer.

They battle over New York City and eventually come to rest at the ruins of Doctor Strange's house. They make amends with each other and return to the Plaza. Ant-Man informs them of a serious seismological problem deep in the Earth. The Surfer agrees to assist them.
name: Down To Earth: 1

story_arc_credits.name: Beware the Rage of a Desperate Man

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Beware the Rage of a Desperate Man

name: Survival of the Fiercest

description: This issue came out in a regular (orange) version and a special variant (green) version which was bagged with a 16 page extra comicbook in it.
name: Live and Let Die, Part One: Darkness Descends
What If Wolverine Battled Weapon X

description: Reprints X-Men #2
name: No One Can Stop The Vanisher!

description: A Shi’ar envoy more or less kidnaps all the X-Men present – in this case Xavier, Storm, Forge and Jubilee – as they are expected to appear at an official royal function on the recently annexed Kree homeworld, Hala!
name: Hard Promises

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Part 3 of the 3-part 'Infestation.' Third Rail, Brickhouse and Kwai join Boogieman in a search through the sewers of Dakota for the White Roach.
name: Infestation, Part 3 - Boogieoogieoogieman
Version 2.0

description: Rocket's crimefighting career could be over after her belt buckle - the source of her powers - is stolen, leaving Icon to stop the thief's violent rampage.
name: Sansabelt

description: Kobalt has been exacting vengeance from Dakota's criminal element for years. When a powerful man calls in a favor, the shadowy avenger must endure his worst nightmare: a SIDEKICK.
name: The Call

description: Following the team's debut during the SHADOW WAR crossover, the Shadow Cabinet - a secret team of heroes with an ongoing mission to save humanity from itself - returns! The first issue reveals glimpses of the Cabinet members' origins, as the team's enigmatic leader Dharma sends team members Iron Butterly, Sideshow, Donner, Blitzen and Plus on an underwater mission that isn't what it seems.
name: A Handful of S.A.N.D.

description: Static puts the brakes on the baddie in style, while Chuck, who insists on below-the-belt humor, gets what's coming to him.
name: Cold-Hearted Snakes

description:
Plot

Two strange and pious investigators named Catholic Girl and Nun of the Above track down a horde of frogs who arrived in this world by way of a teleportational slipstream. After interviewing the frogs at length, they discovered that Doctor Sugarman has escaped.

Meanwhile at Organitek, biochemist David Kim welcomes his new assistant, Kelly Sanborne, to the company. He introduces her to the rest of the staff and shows her his work with nanotechnology. Kim has been working on a process that uses nanites to repair and regrow damaged cell tissue. He takes samples of his own blood and infects them with the Polio virus as part of an experiment to prove the nanites' efficiency.

In another part of the building, the ghosts of insect colonies take the form of an over-sized homunculi, or, "rustling husks" and begin systematically killing all of the company's staff and security guards. The homonculi eventually make their way to David Kim's lab and attack him. The creatures leave Kim for dead and steal a computer disk. As he lies bleeding, Kim has Kelly Sanborne treat him with his nanite-infected blood samples.

The nanites begin restructuring Kim's damaged tissue, but in order for the process to work, the nanites need to assimilate matter from an alternative source. In this case, the source is Kelly Sanborne.
name: Silent Cathedrals Part One: The Rabbit Hole

description:
Oakroot finds a small cat named "Winterleaf" whom he would like to adopt on behalf of the Wolfriders, a dog-loving clan. His patience and charisma is what is needed to overcome the strong distrust element prevalent in most of his tribe. Winterleaf proves his use by killing off poisonous snakes that threaten a young elf-maiden.
He shows personality traits similar to Tyleet (gentleness) and is the only other Wolfrider to have a cat-companion instead of wolf(dog) besides Pike.
name: At The Oak's Root

description:
This issue is concurrent with ElfQuest: Shards by Richard and Wendy Pini. This is where Shuna's father, a centurian for the Grohmul Djun first finds the chache of crystals from the distintegrated palace of The High-Ones.
One very important event occurs when Tyleet, being defended by Aroree sneaks into the human house of Shuna's family. Shuna, dressed in a green shawl, speaks with the elves for the first time, and for the first time, Shuna realises the truth and benevolence of all elves, resolving to help Cutter.
The finality of this episode is Cutter ceremoniously dividing the Wolfriders, leaving his daughter Ember to lead the other half, and giving her a straight dagger of expert metal-smithing from the trolls of Picknose's kingship. Moonshade and Strongbow are split up until ElfQuest: Shards #16 (ElfQuest: Hidden Years #29).
name: SHARDS

description: Two mob families have gone to war -? and young Obadiah Archer is all that stands between them! But when local mafioso Ethan Rosen tries to reward Armstrong's partner-in-training for saving his life, Archer will need to keep one eye on Rosen ? and the other on his back!
name: Bad Karma
Poison

description:
Overview

Supplies are running low at Ice Station Hellman, and the workers are mysteriously dying, infected with a gruesome virus. To add to her troubles, station commander Caroline Konard has offered sanctuary to a renegade Grendel, prompting the station crew to threaten mutiny! This series is written by Steve Seagle, Matt Wagner's collaborator on Sandman Mystery Theatre, and stylishly illustrated by British artist Paul Grist, creator of Kane.

Also in this issue: We meet the mysterious Session Twins in Matt Wagner's painted back-up feature.
name: Chapter 2; Incisionary Tactics Part 1

volume.name: Grendel Tales: The Devil in Our Midst

description: KnightQuest: The Search. Quarry, Part 3 of 3. While Batman is decoyed from coming to his predecessor's aid, Bruce Wayne is captured by Benedict Asp on Santa Prisca during a raging hurricane...meaning Wayne is on his own against Asp and his men as he tries to stop an assassination at the hands of Shondra Kinsolving.
name: Quarry, Part 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
1. Endgame part 1 (Comic)
Cirin and Cerebus are still fighting

2. Endgame part 2 (Text)
Dave Sim puts the reader into the story. Viktor declares this to be his "present" autobiography. He also compares creativity and schizophrenia.

3. Spicy Space Stories (an 8 page  preview by Michael Cohen and  Mark Sherman)
name: Mothers and Daughters 33 : Endgame

description: While Gambit, Yukio, and Storm battle the Phalanx, the others must contend with a host of problems back at the mansion. Bobby, despite having transformed into his ice form, has yet to wake up. And Professor X attempts to cure Sabretooth's bloodlust.
name: Hands Across the Water

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Wolverine has gone to Tokyo to pay his respects to the late Mariko and to check on his surrogate daughter Amiko. It turns out that the people that have been taking care of her have not been treating her very well. Wolverine seeks to change that.

Meanwhile, Bloodscream meets Elsie Dee and Albert in Canada.

On Muir Island, Zoe Culloden informs Moira MacTaggert, Kitty Pryde, and Nightcrawler that she is leaving to pursue some leads that may help Logan.
name: Omnia Mutantur (Everything Changes)

description: "Rake at the Gates of Hell" part 1--the conclusion to Garth Ennis's celebrated run begins here! John Constantine's final battle with the First of the Fallen is joined--and this time the Devil is winning. Now all Constantine's past plans, friends and foes return to haunt him, and even his brazen cunning and razor-edged subtlety may not be enough to outmaneuver his arch nemesis.
name: Rake at the Gates of Hell, Part One

description:
Five years after being pulled into the future, Scott and Jean adopt new names, now going by Slym and Redd Dayspring. But when a mysterious stranger overhears the couple speaking an “olde English” tongue, will their past collide with their present?

Cyclops and Jean Grey have been in the future for five years. Their identities are hidden by the monikers "Slym" and "Redd." They travel to Crestcoast with a young Nathan Christopher in hopes of finding a place to hide from Apocalypse until Nathan is older. Opposition comes, however, when the family tries to enter the city. Some ruffian mutants play with the idea of turning the "Daysprings" in to Apocalypse, but they are saved by a mysterious cyborg named Turrin.
name: Tenure

volume.name: The Adventures of Cyclops and Phoenix

description:
The sinister Senyaka has murderous plans for ship captain Lee Forrester, and the only thing that stands between them is Cable! It's a showdown in the wilderness- but can Cable and Lee make it out alive?

Senyaka is not dead and he is after anyone associated with his former god, Magneto. Current target: Lee Forrester. Cable intercepts the distress signal and the two fight off Senyaka as best as they can. Once the fight is over, though, Cable's gadgets are worthless and the two must find their way through the Everglades.

Synopsis

Lee Forrester huddles in fear as a madman kills every one of her ship's crew. Her S.O.S. to the X-Men seems to have been in vain and she makes a break for the door. A chord wraps around her neck and Lee is brought face-to-face with Senyaka. She shoots him with a flare gun and he hurls her into the Ponce de Leon Bay. Cable pulls her out and begins to question how she was able to send a message directly to the X-Men but is interrupted by the approach of Senyaka.

Senyaka explains that, while his body had been crushed by Magneto and he had been pronounced dead, he had enough of his essence left to absorb the energies of the doctor working on him in the hospital. It was enough to regenerate. Senyaka had then vowed to destroy everything about Magneto, including past lovers - hence the attack on Lee Forrester. Senyaka wraps a chord around Cable's bionic arm and senses life. He attacks and incapacitates Cable's arm. He moves in for the kill but gets blindsided by Lee clubbing him with a branch. She and Cable slink away to come up with a plan.

The two collapse and Lee laments her time with Magneto if it has led to this. Cable explains that the man she knew was different. The two find that they share a mysterious bond as they talk (likely due to the time Lee spent with Cable's father, Cyclops). All the while, Cable tries to repair his arm while breaking up some sticks. Soon enough, Senyaka finds them and grabs Lee. Cable doesn't appear to pose much of a threat, as Senyaka does not know that Cable is a mutant. Cable uses his telekinesis to hurl the broken sticks into Senyaka. Senyaka crumples to the earth and Cable and Lee begin their hike through the woods.
name: Fear and Loathing, Part 1: The Quick and the Dead

description:
Overview

FBI agents Heller and Quillan continue to unravel the mystery that is Enemy, as their investigation slowly reveals an odd, common thread, shared by what seems to be unrelated incidents. It appears that Enemy has a passion for offing members of a super-secret execution squad formed during the Vietnam War. In Denver, Quillan fends off the local police, while nearby some good ol' boys on a race-hate killing spree have some unpaid debts that only the Enemy can collect on. With agent Quillan as the point woman in Colorado, Heller, and his broken arm, have stayed behind to do some digging. And then, all hell breaks loose!
Arcadia is in flames as X battles his deadliest foes yet -- the Chaos Riders! Seemingly unstoppable, the mysterious Riders have a vulnerable point, but will X find it before it's too late?
name: Riders Of The Storm

description: The enabler has been stolen and is now intended to be developped for human warfair. While Catwoman is fighting to get it back, she has to confront the Tin Man, a special soldier with bio-prosthetic arms and body...
name: Tin Men

description: Scarab and Eleanor's destinies come together in this finale, as she is reborn and must come to terms with what and who her husband truly is.
name: What the Rabbit Saw
Bad Blood!

description:
(continued from Batman 508)
Kitch reported to Gordon that Batman let Abattoir die. The search for Graham Etchison (Abattoir's hostage) continued. He was found dead in Abattoir's torture device. Gordon called in Batman and confronted him. Az-Bat played off the "murder" and left. He took down a street gang and headed back to the cave to modify the bat suit again.
(continued in Detective 675)
name: Commissioner Gordon: The Long Dark Night

description:
"The Battle for Metropolis" part 2. The "Lex-men" take on the "Dubbilex-men" of Project Cadmus as the clone war of Metropolis rages on. Now the city is being evacuated and Guardian falls trying to protect innocent people.

Innocent clones are in danger as the remains of the city are fought over by power-hungry, armed groups.

Notes:

  • "War" (Superman) written by Louise Simonson, penciled by Jon Bogdanove, inked by Dennis Janke, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by Ken Lopez.
  • "The Call" (Kobalt) written by John Rozum, penciled by Arvell Jones, inked by John Stanisci, painted color by David Montoya and lettered by Steve Dutro. A Milestone Preview of Kolbalt #1.
  • "DC Universe 17" "From the DC High 1994 Yearbook" one page featuring Damage by Bill Marimon and Tom McWeeney, the Ray by Joe Quesada, Anima by Steve Crespo and Chris Ivy, Superboy by Tom Grummett and Doug Hazlewood, Robin by Tom Grummett and Scott Hanna and a good luck note from "Principal Carlin". Each character featured: Voted, Afterschool Activities, Quote and Immediate Plans.
  • 40 page issue.
  • Triangle 1994 #21.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #699.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #90.
name: War / The Call

description: Dr. Maxilla Yale brings Anima back to the Tellus Institute to reunite with her mother. Both she and her mother continue to have dreams about a giant wolf named Fenris and Anima’s alter-ego Animus, and Yale experiments on a willing Anima to discover the truth about the dreams. Yale brings Anima to a spiritual location in the desert, where Yale tricks Anima into releasing Animus. However, in doing so, Animus is pulled from its native dimension Arkana, leaving the Fenris wolf alone fighting something called the Nameless One. In Arkana, the Nameless One kills Fenris, which also causes Willow Mason to be trapped in her dreams. Nameless One follows Animus to our world, where Anima and Animus fight Nameless One. Anima draws energy from Yale, causing her to age. Meanwhile, the battle attracts the attention of others, including Anima’s brother Jeremy, Agent Kyle Woodleaf, and other residents of Arkana.
name: Break Out

description: The War on Weber's World escalates as one Legion member makes a noble sacrifice to ensure peace. Plus, anomalies within the timestream lead to a surprising alliance.
name: Down to the Wire

description:
This issue came out in a regular version and a special variant (gold) version which was bagged with a 16 page extra comicbook in it.

Still reeling from the death of his parents, Peter struggles to find purpose as Spider-Man. Carrion faces his own guilt from past sins, while Shriek flies off the handle! Who will pay the price?

Shrieking Part One - Still reeling from the revelation that Harry Osborne attacked Peter from beyond the grave, Peter must face increasing tensions in his marriage and a prophetic dream of his impending doom from Aunt May. As if this isn't enough, Vermin has found Shriek and has plans for her... Can Peter survive?
name: Shrieking, Part One: Behind the Walls

description:
Supreme Madness Part 2: Union investigates about a huge explosion in Washington. In fact, he is the first who discover Supreme after the experience of Grizlock. The mad man believes everybody is his arch-enemy and attacks Union. 
The battle is terrible between the two powerful being even if Union tries to reason Supreme.   
Finally,  Union  takes a blast from Supreme and falls down. Satisfied, Supreme flies away. But,  when Jill Monroe runs to helps Union, she discovers that Union has pretended to loose in order to stop the bottle. 
but the supreme's madness isn't finished.
name: Supreme Madness, Part 2

description: Jason Blood has opened a portal to Hell in order to spy on the Demon. But when Gotham City Detective Joe Gun stumbles on the portal, his unscheduled visit to Hades gets him a ringside seat for an Unblessed Event: the infernal birth of Etrigan's son!
name: From Hell

description: Femforce leader Ms. Victory is the star in the new lead story, as she runs up against a displaced former Communist agent, who has no intention of stopping her war on democracy, just because the U.S.S.R. is no more, in "Cold -Warrior in Sunny Florida", with script and art by Richard(The Count)Rome (from a plot by Mark Heike) and inks by Chris Allen. Introduces the villainess Cherry Bomb. Then the Golden Age section features two old favorites, and two newcomers. Fox Feature's Phantom Lady is back, in "The Fat Connoisseur!", and Fiction House's Sky Gal(Girl), in a story drawn by that ultimate purveyor of "good girl art", Matt Baker. New to GGAQ this issue are Magazine Enterprises' Cave Girl, in "The Devil Boat", with art by Bob Powell, and Avon's Dara Of The Vikings. Color cover by Mark Heike, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52 pages, standard comic book format.
name: Cold-Warrior in Sunny Florida

description:
Overview

Who is Ralph Rowan? Who is Gideon Longshadow? And what is their interest in the fabulous Babe? Since Babe doesn't know herself, she can't tell them. Babe doesn't know where she came from, how she ended up on the beach, why she's so incredibly strong, why nothing hurts her, or why she can... breathe underwater? Can't everybody?

From the world of John Byrne's Danger Unlimited comes a woman who walks out of the waves and into the wild world of southern California, wearing nothing more than an enigmatic smile for the sleazy Hollywood agent who sees in her not his wildest dreams, not his ultimate fantasy -- but a nuisance interrupting his busy day.

Badger, the multi-faceted hero with the multiple personality disorder! He pops out his head for the first time in years in this revealing origin story, featuring the return of Ham the Weather Wizard, Badger's medieval Welsh druid buddy. The pair are trapped in a modern-day American mental hospital, or are they? It looks as though the inmates are making their bid to run the asylum! With one thinking he's more men than man and the other going through a Middle Ages life crisis.

Overview

When your back's up to the wall and your very soul's at stake; when the fate of the universe rests in your hands and the entire Empire's looking to disarm you; you can fold like a house of cards or you can use a little Force. Reprinted from the original Marvel Star Wars series, this is the second of two newly colored, prestige-format issues bringing the first Star Wars movie to comic books. Thrill to the adventures of Luke and Leia, the swashbuckling Han Solo and his trusted companion Chewbacca, the dastardly Darth Vader, and the faithful droids Artoo-Detoo and See-Threepio. The fact that this is the first time in over a decade this has seen print and the cover by fan-favorite Adam Hughes ensures that this will be a brand-new comic for today's fans!
name: Book Two

volume.name: Classic Star Wars: A New Hope

description:
Overview
All Larry Munro wanted was a tank of gas. What he gotwas a gun put to his head. Now he's being forced to play chauffeur to a pyromaniac looking to burn LA to the ground! Can a 1200-pound Concrete race fast enough to stop the bullet aimed at his best friend's head? Legend creator Paul Chadwick takes Concrete to a new level of art and a new level of action in this four-issue series. Don't miss this next step in the evolution of the most acclaimed comics character of the past ten years! If you want to Make The Break from the same old thing, you've got to start with a Killer Smile!

Overview

The Way of the Flesh, a mysterious and twisted cult, has targeted Steel Harbor and -- worse -- the Hammerhead Bar as its latest conquest. But the Hammerhead has its own defender: Avram Roman, better known as The Machine! This issue of Dark Horse Comics brings you part 1 of "The Machine: Under My Skin," written by Eric Luke and pencilled by Howard Cobb. If you haven't tried the Comics' Greatest World line of superheroes, here's your opportunity!

Also, don't miss part 2 of "Aliens: Mondo Pest." A wounded Herk Mondo escapes from the underground hive, but finds the terraformer colony overrun with Aliens!

Paul Chadwick's back, with an all-new companion tale to his remarkable new miniseries Concrete: Killer Smile. Don't miss this exciting introduction, by one of Legend's most respected creators.

Lord Parsons accuses Master Architect Overton of murder most foul in the thrilling conclusion to our cover story, "The Eighth Wonder," but when Dr. Agrine -- the victim -- appears, all hell breaks loose in the most amazing chase scene in comics' history!

Looking forward to the future's Information Highway? Beware! Rick Geary's "The Phantom Telephone" reveals the insidious terror that lurks beneath that brushed steel!

Also in this issue, during the breathless finale of "Star Riders," we finally get to see what Tabada wears under that miniskirt!

Chapters

  • The Eighth Wonder - Part 3 (of 3)
  • Concrete
  • Home Remedy
  • Standing on the Line
  • Yes, It Happened
  • The Phantom Telephone
  • Star Riders - Part 3 (of 3)
name: The Eighth Wonder; Concrete; Rick Geary; Star Riders

description: In the explosive conclusion to "Hell on Earth," Jonny literally goes to Hell to stop the Storm of a Thousand Shadows! Kodiak Joe, Candleshoe the Vampire, and the anti-demon resistance fight a last-ditch battle against the demon sorceress Sharaka while Jonny battles to free a trapped soul -- if they fail it means the destruction of every human mind on earth. With salvation clutched in his hand and a humongous, soul-devouring Ur-demon breathing down his neck, the one thing he won't die from is boredom!

Overview

Following in the tradition of all great American heroes, Martha Washington goes on a road trip. But rather than heading out on US1 or Route 66, Martha follows the call of the road into the heart of the Radioactive Zone, where she is surrounded by deadly, but somehow lovable, mutants.
name: The Valley of Death

description: The Shadow is racing against time as Shiwan Khan plans to destroy New York City with Reinhardt Lane's superbomb. Only the Shadow, aided by his trusty team of secret operatives, can prevent the catastrophe! But to do so, the Shadow must take on Shiwan Khan's Mongolian guards, Rienhardt Lane's corrupt assistant Claymore, a drugged Margo Lane, and Shiwan Khan himself -- the only man on earth with mental powers as strong as -- if not stronger than -- the Shadow's.

When Star Wars hit the big screen in 1977, the world fell in love with Artoo-Detoo and See-Threepio. Now the events that led them to their fateful meeting with Luke Skywalker are revealed for the first time! In this issue, Corellian rogue Jace Forno leases the dysfunctional duo for a deadly mission to the moon Indobok!

Part 4 of the 5-part 'The Fall of Metropolis.' Nerve gas is released to ensure that all living things remaining in Metropolis won't last long...unless Superman can overcome his deepest fears when he encounters Luthor's third fail-safe.

Notes:

  • Lois Lane, Jonathan and Martha Kent appear as hallucinations.
  • Triangle 1994 #27.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #91.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #701.
name: Dangerous Visions

description: Buddy and Maxine make their TV talk show debut to promote the Life-Power Church of Maxine as Ellen heads to Oregon, grappling with her decision to leave her family.
name: Children And Animals

description: Knights End: Part One. Bruce Wayne tries to regain his fighting spirit by training with Lady Shiva. Problem, he cannot trust her.
name: Spirit of the Bat

description:
Batman confronts his old friend-turned-enemy Two-Face, who has escaped from prison.

This issue is set some time after Two-faces debut on Batman: The animated series (1992).

Two-face escapes from Arkham Asulym, and plans to rise up as the criminal lord of Gotham city!
name: Good Face Bad Face

description: Suzy, the young Black Orchid, escapes Free Country and pursues the traitorous trickster, Junkin Buckley, through the Nexus. And Black Orchid, newly enlightened about her heritage, returns to Tennessee to tell Nick of Sherilyn's fate.
name: Suzy and the Trade of Fates

description:
Part 3 of the 3-part "Bindings." Timothy Hunter risks everything to save Faerie from the Manticore's conjurings, but the scant magic Tim has learned may not be enough to save his life.

Tamlin reminisces on his life as a human, before he was seduced by Titania and brought to live in Faerie, a realm which is now falling apart. In the form of a falcon, he seeks the source of the destruction.

Tim plays hide and seek with the Manticore, in a dangerous game with high stakes. He is spurred on as he sees others who lost against the Manticore, and are now taxidermied specimens in his collection.

Tim finds a picture of a manticore in the library and realizes what he is. The Manticore finds him and explains more about how he is removing extraneous objects, like the unicorn, from reality. He explains that he wants to show that things like the unicorn aren't real, aren't magic, and are just hoaxes--by "disproving" them, he takes their souls and removes them from reality.

The Manticore leaves, saying the game hadn't yet begun, and that he'd be back. Tim talks to the stuffed unicorn specimen, consoling himself.

The Manticore returns in its beats form, and bites Tim, but the unicorn comes alive, inspired by Tim's feelings for it, and stabs the manticore book page, killing the creature. The unicorn leaves.

Tim walks off, dripping blood from his hand. The drips of blood turn into flowers on the ground, and soon all of Faerie is blooming again. It was the Manticore that was draining it.

Tamlin finds Tim, who is fainting. He knows the Manticore's bite is poisonous. As Tim passes out, he sees the figure of Death.
name: Bindings, Book III: Closing Circles

description: A powerless Damage must stop Troll before Atlanta is destroyed by their battle. Then the powerful new metahuman Wyldheart appears to tip the scales in Damage's favor...but she may prove to be more foe than friend. Plus, the identity of the mysterious Golden Age hero is revealed.
name: Troll's Day

description: In the rubble-strewn aftermath of the Teiresias Wars, an alienated Dorothy follows Charlie the seedy doll into a strange world to free a soul imprisoned and guarded by yapping dogs.
name: The Dogs of Soul

description: Fighting American is in the fight of his life as he learns at last the truth about his origin and the identity of the mastermind behind the villains who have been plaguing him.
name: The Fighting Ugly American

description: "Reckless Youth" Part 1! Meet the newest member of the Flash family! Iris Allen arrives from the future, bringing with her a special someone. This issue features the first appearance of Impulse, an important player in the DCU for years to come!
name: Reckless Youth Part 1: Speed Kills

description:
Kyle is about to die when SUPERMAN comes to his rescue. While supes tangles with Mongul. Kyle is roused by Alex and jumps right back into the fight, only to be tossed away like so much trash. Supes and mongul continue to battle as Alex worries for Kyle. Kyle jumps back in the fight again and send Mongul flying. While the trio fights Supes wants to know who Kyle is, Kyle says GL obviously, supes says not the one I know. They banter about Mongul and his mad on for GL the old one. Supes says Mongul doesn’t really care if he’s the same guy he just wants to kill him.

Supes takes over the battle as Kyle gets his bearings, Alex eggs him on to do something BIG. While he’s kinda in awe that THE superman is here helping him. In the end Kyle drops Mongul with a well placed subway train that literally steal rolls him. Supes commends him on his ring skills despite Kyle’s obliviousness to who the guardians and the corps. are. Supes say link him whenever he’s in Metroplis and Alex and Kyle watch supes carry off Mongul to parts unknown. Kyle realizes he really can do this hero bit

Back at creepy place the dude who got the green rock has tried everything to cut it, dissect it, or just test the darn thing to no avail. He turns it over to Major force and hands him a file with all the info gathered on the new GL. Major force only wants to know, do they want just the ring or his whole hand?
name: Rematch

description: Part 3 of the 5-part 'Godspawn.' Hawkman meets Hawkman as the Golden Age Hawkman joins Katar Hol's hunt for Bad Blood and his new ally - Mongrel! Meanwhile, the countdown to ZERO HOUR continues as Katar Hol's mother charts the relentless progress of the Hawkgod as it speeds toward Earth...and Hawkman.
name: Godspawn, Part 3: Bird's-eye View

description:
The Huntress' identity is uncovered by a Gotham City cop who may try to use that information to control her. Plus, still haunted by a specter from the past, the Huntress comes face to face with the deadly assassin known only as Redzone.

The Huntress has her secret identity discovered and she is hunted by Redzone as she is haunted by the Smiling Man. Batman only appears in this book briefly and has no speaking role.
name: Breaking Cover

description: Judgment Day, part 4 of 6. Captain Atom’s team of Justice Leaguers have defeated half of the Overmaster’s Cadre, but now they face the U.N. sanctioned Leaguebusters: the new Peacemaker, the second Mirror Master, the second Spellbinder, Ultraa, and Chromax. Wonder Woman and Power Girl discover the existence of the Leaguebusters, and confront Maxwell Lord, announcing that the Justice League will sever its relations with the U.N. After a long fight, Captain Atom’s team defeats the Leaguebusters, but they are prevented from continuing on by Wonder Woman’s team. Meanwhile, at the Overmaster’s ship, the Cadre (now led by a mind-controlled Ice) has captured Fire; and back at S.T.A.R. Labs, Blue Beetle has crafted a cybernetic arm for Booster Gold. Beetle also repairs Booster Gold’s battle armor, and Beetle comes up with a plan to stop the Overmaster. The two travel to Mount Everest, and arrive just in time to diffuse the situation between Captain Atom and Wonder Woman. The League reunites as Beetle fills them in on his plan to stop the Overmaster.
name: Judgment Day, Part 4: The Shadow of Death

description: Judgment Day, part 6 of 6. With the death of Ice at the Overmaster’s hand, the Justice League pushes their assault. The remaining Leaguers let loose at the Overmaster, but the giant alien shrugs their attacks off. While most of the Leaguers focus on Overmaster, Blue Beetle peels off to disable the Overmaster’s bomb. Though he finds Overmaster’s bomb guarded by the ship’s pilot, Beetle is able to elude the pilot long enough to disarm the bomb, but not before he draws Overmaster’s attention. Overmaster heads to try to stop Beetle, and triggers the bomb to explode early, but Booster Gold catches his attention. Amazing-Man then absorbs some of Overmaster’s power, and fights the Overmaster one-on-one. Amazing-Man defeats the Overmaster, and Blue Beetle channels the bomb to destroy the Overmaster’s landed ship. The Leaguers get into an escape pod, use a tractor beam to rescue the other members of the League, and escape the explosion. However, with the Overmaster down, his effect that causes all the births and deaths on Earth to stop ends. Booster drops to the ground, dead. Beetle, however, had rigged a life support system in Booster’s new armor. He activates the resuscitator, brings Booster back to life. The Overmaster has been stopped, but not without its price, as the league retrieve the dead body of Ice.
name: All Out of Time

description: Judgment Day, part 5 of 6. With Bloodwynd, T.O. Morrow, and Vandal Savage watching on the sidelines, the Justice League begins their final assault on the Overmaster’s base. They break up into three teams, led by Wonder Woman, Captain Atom, and Metamorpho. They begin their assault, and find themselves up against the Cadre. Along the way, many Leaguers and their allies fall to either the snowstorm or to the Cadre, including Metamorpho sacrificing himself for his team, and Gypsy left buried beneath a snow drift. All the while, T.O. Morrow watches the future he witnessed play out in front of him. By the time they reach the top, only a small group remains: Amazing-Man, Blue Beetle, Booster Gold, Captain Atom, Flash, Martian Manhunter, and Wonder Woman. They find Ice waiting for them, but Martian Manhunter manages to break through Overmaster’s control. Meanwhile, Fire manages to break free from her captivity, and, with her fire powers restored, she joins the other Leaguers. The League assaults Overmaster, who kills Ice immediately for her betrayal of the Cadre.
name: Judgment Day, Part 5: The Longest Yard

description: Part 2 of 4. Kid Eternity has entered into a bargain with Beelzebub to find five truly evil men in order to keep the devil from destroying Earth. While the Kid embarks on his mission, his date Chelsea wanders Hell's Terminal Lounge and starts making trouble.
name: The Devil's Last Stand

description:
The subject is time. Cosmic Boy, Saturn Girl and Live Wire are traveling through it. Brainiac 5 and Invisible Kid penetrate some mysteries about it, and some surprising characters pop out of it!

Members of the Legionnaires, including Cosmic Boy, Saturn Girl, Live Wire, Apparition and Triad, discover anomalies in their time period, including different team members and members who others believe are dead but shouldn't be. Invisible Kid and Rond Vidar, Brainiac 5's scientific assistant, appear to understand what's going on but refrain from telling anyone.
name: Saved by Zero

description: Bruce Wayne dons the Batman costume again, though Jean-Paul Valley is still active.
name: KnightsEnd Part Five: Death's Door

description: Lives are shattered and left in ruin as the Golden Age Sandman reveals the identity of the elusive Vamp, while the course of Dian Belmont and Wesley Dodds's relationship takes an unexpected turn.
name: The Vamp: Final Act

description:
As Lyta's journey continues, her friends begin to piece together clues regarding her disappearance--which unfortunately catches the attention of one of the story's key players. "The Kindly Ones" part 5.

Dream sends the Corintian and Matthew to seek for Daniel. Lyta Hall finds the furies. Rose receives a message from her late grandmother. Loki has plans for Carla.
name: The Kindly Ones, Part 5

description: Part 5 of the 6-part 'A Season in Hell.' Kathy broods through the final days of her pregnancy, pondering her distressing past, her unpredictable present and her uncertain future.
name: A Season in Hell, Part Five

description: Spock returns to Talos IV to offer his former captain Christopher Pike the chance of release from his crippled body and his illusory existence...but a surprise waits to greet Spock on his arrival.
name: Door In The Cage

description: Part 3 of 3. In "Brothers in Darkness," Picard searches for a way to rescue the members of Riker's away team and a Chalnoth landing party, who are entombed by a marauding creature on the planet's surface. And adding to the pressure are the four Chalnoth ships surrounding the Enterprise!
name: Brothers in Darkness

volume.name: Star Trek: The Next Generation Special

description:
Superboy must face his biggest challenge yet when he goes toe-to-toe with the Parasite, a creature that has almost killed the Man of Steel on several occasions. Plus, Superboy meets Fred Bentson from the Milestone Universe!

Superboy finds a confused man and also finds a monster seeking him parasite! Will Superboy be able to defeat a villian even Superman had trouble with?
name: Worlds Collide, Part 3:  Changing Relaties

description: Following the startling events of 'Bad Gumbo,' a strangely changed Swamp Thing travels to New York City where he encounters a dead priest who walks the earth. But the Parliament of Trees - and others - are pursuing the Earth Elemental, each with their own agendas.
name: A Hope in Hell
